# Input file for DRIFTORBIT - Version 1.2
# 
#
0.62         s                  - Radial coordinate of banana tips, s = sphi(pphi)  
0.05         M_t		        - Mach number (for single Mach no. run)
1d0          qi                 - species charge
2.014        mi                 - species mass
1d19		 n0		            - particle density
1e7          vth		        - thermal velocity
1e-3         epsmn              - perturbation amplitude B1/B0 (when pertfile==F)
0		     m		            - poroidal perturbation mode (when pertfile==F)
2 		     n		            - toroidal perturbation mode (when pertfile==F, MUST BE > 0)
0		     mth		        - poloidal canonical mode (for single Mach no. run)
10       	 mthnum	            - poloidal canonical mode count
0d0	    	 Mtmin	            - minimum Mach number
0d0	    	 Mtmax	            - maximum Mach number
1            Mtnum              - Mach number count
F            supban             - calculate superbanana plateau only
T		     magdrift	        - consider magnetic drift
F		     nopassing	        - neglect passing particles
F		     calcflux	        - calculate flux directly instead via flux-force relation
F		     noshear            - neglect magnetic shear term with dqds
F		     pertfile           - read perturbation from file with neo_magfie_pert
F            odeint             - use ODE integrator for resonance line
F            nonlin             - compute nonlinear attenuation
1.0          bscale             - scale B field
1.0          escale             - scale E field
8            in_swi             - input switch for magfie files
0            orbit_mode_avg     - orbit integration for bounce average. 0: zero order, 1: first order
0            orbit_mode_transp  - orbit integration for transport. 0: zero order, 1: first order
128          vsteps             - integration steps in velocity space. 0: adaptive integration, works only with orbit_mode_transp=0
T		     comptorque         - compute torque directly instead of transport coefficients D11 and D12
T            intoutput          - output sub-integrand and resonance parameters

